Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 11/30/98

Got some cycle counts for decoding.  I decoded a Hits, 1/2 D1 P picture from
the simulator and it took about 67M cycles.  For a 200 MHz DSP targetting to
decode at 10 P frames per second, this is about 3.5 times to real time.
For D1 resolution at 10 frames/sec, the decoder needs at least 7 times
improvement.

Trying to get familar with the C6x instruction set.

